 {"id":"bd-ty7","title":"Website parity + implementation master epic for mcp_agent_mail_rust","description":"Build a full Next.js website for mcp_agent_mail_rust modeled after /dp/asupersync_website in stack, structure, component patterns, and interaction style, while adapting copy, diagrams, and visualizations to the Agent Mail Rust domain.\\n\\nThis master plan is exhaustive and now includes a dedicated automated-test matrix for comprehensive unit tests, end-to-end scripts, and detailed diagnostics logging artifacts.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-04T18:59:58.673115070Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-05T03:11:13.368859307Z","closed_at":"2026-03-05T03:11:13.368844409Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":10,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Background and Intent\nThis master epic exists to satisfy a high-bar request: build the `mcp_agent_mail_rust` website with near-total structural parity to `/dp/asupersync_website` while replacing content with Agent Mail Rust-specific material grounded in repository truth.\n\n# Scope Boundaries\n- In scope: stack parity, route parity, reusable component parity, content adaptation, interactive technical visualizations, QA, launch readiness.\n- Out of scope: speculative feature invention not justified by README/code/docs.\n\n# Planning Standard\nAll downstream beads must be execution-ready, self-contained, and source-grounded so future agents can implement without re-reading the original prompt.\n","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:01:02Z"},{"id":11,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Plan-space review revision\nThis graph was reviewed and revised to improve execution quality without losing scope:\n- Added a dedicated automated-testing subtree (unit + E2E + diagnostics logging).\n- Reduced unnecessary QA serialization to improve parallel throughput.\n- Preserved all original feature/content/visualization scope.\n- Strengthened launch gates with explicit test orchestration dependency.\n","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:09:56Z"},{"id":12,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Optimization pass 5\\nAdded dedicated marketing/conversion beads, frankentui pattern extraction, homepage centerpiece video placeholder planning, and corresponding unit/E2E/diagnostics gates to improve product presentation quality without removing existing functionality.","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:30:16Z"},{"id":13,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Optimization pass 6\\nAdded storyboard/recording-brief, transcript/chapter, social-proof, structured-data SEO, and dedicated validation beads so the site can match top-tier marketing quality while remaining technically rigorous and testable.","created_at":"2026-03-04T22:10:37Z"},{"id":14,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Coordination update:\n\n- Completed and closed `bd-ty7.1.1` (reference architecture/component inventory).\n- Unblocked path now moves through:\n  - `bd-ty7.2.1` (stack/config parity port from asupersync)\n  - `bd-ty7.1.2` (README/docs narrative extraction)\n  - `bd-ty7.1.3` (mechanism-level code truth extraction)\n  - `bd-ty7.1.6` (frankentui conversion pattern extraction)\n- Recommended parallel split for fellow agents:\n  1) Agent A: `bd-ty7.1.2`\n  2) Agent B: `bd-ty7.1.3`\n  3) Agent C: `bd-ty7.1.6`\n  4) Me: begin `bd-ty7.2.1` implementation scaffold in this repo.\n\nNote: Agent Mail endpoint currently unreachable (`127.0.0.1:8765/api`), so this coordination is captured in beads comments to preserve shared state.\n","created_at":"2026-03-04T22:43:03Z"},{"id":15,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Starting implementation bead bd-ty7.2.1 now: porting asupersync stack/config scaffold into this repo as the base for Agent Mail content/viz adaptation.","created_at":"2026-03-04T22:54:16Z"},{"id":16,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Coordination update: scaffold epic bd-ty7.2 is now closed. Newly unblocked high-priority streams are bd-ty7.3 (IA/routes) and bd-ty7.5 (interactive visualization suite). Current codebase now builds cleanly and includes initial Agent Mail onboarding content on /getting-started.","created_at":"2026-03-04T23:01:46Z"},{"id":17,"issue_id":"bd-ty7","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Completed bd-ty7.3.2 route scaffold pass; this unblocks route composition beads and Playwright harness setup dependent on stable section anchors.","created_at":"2026-03-04T23:29:31Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-ty7.1","title":"Research & traceability dossier (asupersync parity + agent-mail-rust truth)","description":"Produce a comprehensive analysis package mapping reusable reference-site patterns and Agent Mail Rust source truth into implementation-ready guidance.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:01:03.158995437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-04T22:53:56.309960663Z","closed_at":"2026-03-04T22:53:56.309943992Z","close_reason":"Research dossier complete: asupersync parity, Agent Mail narrative + mechanism truth, and conversion patterns captured","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-ty7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-ty7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T17:10:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":18,"issue_id":"bd-ty7.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Why this exists\nFactual rigor and implementation fidelity depend on analysis quality. This epic creates the canonical dossier used by all downstream work.\n\n# Deliverables\n- Reference-site pattern inventory.\n- Agent Mail Rust content/feature inventory.\n- Code-level mechanism map for visualization design.\n- Claim-to-source traceability matrix.\n","created_at":"2026-03-04T19:01:03Z"},{"id":19,"issue_id":"bd-ty7.1","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"# Decomposition rationale\\nResearch was split into reference-pattern inventory, content extraction, and code-mechanism extraction before traceability synthesis. This ordering prevents two common failures: (1) building a pretty clone with wrong technical claims, and (2) writing accurate copy but losing the visual/system interaction quality of the reference website.\\n\\n# Risk controls\\n- R4 claim matrix is the factual gate for downstream copy.\\n- R5 prioritization prevents visualization scope explosion.\\n\\n# Completion standard\\nDownstream teams should be able to execute without re-reading READM